---

The gentle breeze, a lover's sigh,
In meadows wide, where memories lie;
The colors paint a world divine,
In nature's art, our hearts entwine.

Each moment cherished, softly held,
As seasons change, our spirits meld;
For in the dance of time and space,
We find our home in nature's grace.

- Price Day
